    <briefdescription>
<para>Ramp / motion profile generator. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Generates smooth setpoint transitions for any controlled variable (valves, lights, temperature, motor speed, etc.).</para>
<para>Supports two modes:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>LINEAR: constant slew rate</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>TRAPEZOID: acceleration/deceleration (trapezoidal velocity profile)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>The trapezoid mode supports optional fixed-point velocity/acceleration via <computeroutput><ref refid="syn__ramp_8h_1a6cf8bcdc5048165203390d4cc51cdc20" kindref="member">syn_ramp_set_target_trapezoid_fp()</ref></computeroutput>. This allows sub-unit-per-tick resolution — critical when converting from per-second to per-tick at high update rates where integer truncation would lose precision.</para>
<para>Usage: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="structSYN__Ramp" kindref="compound">SYN_Ramp</ref><sp/>ramp;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__ramp_8c_1a52d1c828ac89b45a17be1736863bfc04" kindref="member">syn_ramp_init</ref>(&amp;ramp,<sp/>0);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__ramp_8c_1ab37da99a5fb59848009175e850fa596d" kindref="member">syn_ramp_set_target</ref>(&amp;ramp,<sp/>1000,<sp/>10);<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>ramp<sp/>to<sp/>1000<sp/>at<sp/>10/tick</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>In<sp/>your<sp/>update<sp/>loop:</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">int32_t<sp/>output<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="syn__ramp_8c_1a03caa503aa8f8dfbb8e680e259a600ec" kindref="member">syn_ramp_update</ref>(&amp;ramp);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
